reenwood (Oct. 20, EF1)}}\n|{{Sort|002|October&nbsp;20}}\n|01:42\u201301:49\n|{{convert|3.59|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|350|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|A greenhouse was destroyed, shingled were ripped off the roofs of two homes, and an RV trailer was rolled onto its side. Numerous trees were snapped or uprooted.\n|<ref>{{cite report|agency=National Weather Service Weather Forecast Office in Shreveport, Louisiana|title=Louisiana Event Report: EF1 Tornado|url=https://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/stormevents/eventdetails.jsp?id=855002|publisher=National Centers for Environmental Information|year=2019|accessdate=January 21, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|bgcolor={{storm colour|cat3}} | EF3\n|[[Dallas, Texas|Dallas]] to [[Richardson, Texas|Richardson]]\n|[[Dallas County, Texas|Dallas]]\n|[[Texas|TX]]\n|{{Coord|32.8685|-96.9149|name=Dallas (Oct. 20, EF3)}}\n|{{Sort|003|October&nbsp;20}}\n|01:58\u201302:30\n|{{convert|15.76|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|1300|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|[[Tornado outbreak of October 20\u201322, 2019#Dallas-Richardson, Texas|See section on this tornado]]\n|<ref name=\"dallas\" />\n|-\n|bgcolor={{storm colour|cat1}} | EF1\n|N of [[Midlothian, Texas|Midlothian]]\n|[[Ellis County, Texas|Ellis]]\n|[[Texas|TX]]\n|{{Coord|32.4981|-96.9935|name=Midlothian (Oct. 20, EF1)}}\n|{{Sort|004|October&nbsp;20}}\n|02:10\u201302:15\n|{{convert|2.83|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|350|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|Several church and retail buildings had their roofs damaged and windows blown out. One structure attached to the church was severely damaged as most of its roof was ripped off, and its south-facing wall was collapsed. Two buildings had sheet metal peeled away, while one of the structures had its metal roof purlins bent. Several homes suffered significant roof damage and had windows blown out, one  of which had its garage door collapsed. Trees were snapped or uprooted as well.\n|<ref>{{cite report|agency=National Weather Service Weather Forec